Halfhand records AI agent sessions to a local SQLite database and
replays them faithfully. All data stays on your machine;
Halfhand makes zero network calls (SRS NFR-2).

Recorded sessions can contain secrets present in prompts and
outputs — use `hh delete` to remove them.

Usage: hh <COMMAND>

Commands:
  run          Record an agent session inside a PTY (SRS FR-1)
  replay       Faithfully play back a recorded session in an interactive TUI (SRS FR-3)
  inspect      Print non-interactive detail about a session (SRS FR-4)
  list         List recorded sessions, newest first (SRS FR-5)
  delete       Delete a session and garbage-collect its blobs (SRS FR-6.1)
  mcp-proxy    Run an MCP server behind a recording stdio proxy (SRS FR-2)
  doctor       Diagnose the recording stack and report pass/fail per check
  gc           Reclaim disk space: prune orphaned blobs and vacuum the database (Area 3)
  stats        Summarize the store: sessions, events, disk usage, largest sessions (Area 3)
  scan         Scan recorded sessions for secrets (docs/redaction.md)
  redact       Irreversibly redact secrets from a recorded session in place
  export       Export a session as a JSON bundle, a portable `.hh` archive, or a self-contained HTML page
  import       Import a portable session bundle produced by `hh export --bundle`
  search       Search recorded sessions for text matches (FTS5 full-text search)
  completions  Print a shell completion script for `hh` (FR-6.2 ergonomics)
  help         Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version

Examples:
  hh run -- claude              record a Claude Code session
  hh replay last                 replay the most recent session
  hh inspect a1b2c3 --json       print session detail as JSON
  hh list                        list recorded sessions
